    "body": "Changes to implementation:\r\n1. Change to parser to allow `case +0.2:` or `case 1 - +0.2j` or `case 1 + +0.2j`. This is a 3.15 update to the allowed syntax.\r\n2. Changes to type-checking code for match class. In Cython's rules, setting the type to `type` meant \"exact instance of `type`\" rather than \"any subtype of `type`\". This meant that we were failing to check `Protocol` correctly.  This changes some checks to a less efficient full `isinstance` check, but the common case where the type is known at compile time remains good.\r\n\r\nPart of #4029",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-16T16:49:25Z",
